President Biden has declared a major disaster in Delaware due to the remnants of Hurricane Ida. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Mark Kenneth O'Hanlon has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.